gstat - package gstat
A package designed to allow for the gathering of game statistics.
gstat.premade - package gstat.premade
A variety of common games complete with implementation, AI, and built-in statistics to demonstrate the abilities of the gstat package.
gstat.premade.blackjack - package gstat.premade.blackjack
Demonstrates the API's use of tokens and basic playing cards.
gstat.premade.exampleclasses - package gstat.premade.exampleclasses
This package provides simple examples of classes being implemented using the gstat package.
gstat.premade.playingcard - package gstat.premade.playingcard
A standard 52 card playing card deck implemented according to the requirements of gstat.util.Card.
gstat.premade.shutthebox - package gstat.premade.shutthebox
The game shut the box involves rolling two six sided dice and using a set of tiles numbered one to nine.
gstat.premade.uno - package gstat.premade.uno
This package holds several files that help to create a simulation of the popular card game UNO.
gstat.premade.war - package gstat.premade.war
A package that simulates the card game War, a game in which two players simultaneously flip cards from their deck and the highest card wins both cards played until one player has all the cards.
gstat.util - package gstat.util
This package provides the necessary components of a wide variety of card games.
